# Axis 6 — zero-resume (early return / abort)

A handler arm that returns WITHOUT invoking `resume` — the exception-like case
(§14.1 "zero-, one-, and many-resume handlers"). The suffix after the perform
(`x + 100`) never runs; the handler's value replaces the whole computation.

```scalascript
effect Fail:
  def raise(): Int

def prog(): Int =
  val x = Fail.raise()
  x + 100

val r = handle(prog()) {
  case Fail.raise(resume) => -1
  case Return(x) => x
}
println(r)
```
